local/
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.webp
*.gif
*.aseprite
*.tsx
*.tmx
*.json
!asset_manifest.example.json
!README.md
# Foundry MAI-generated art is ours and ships under MIT (see generated/CREDITS.md).
!generated/
!generated/*.png
!generated/CREDITS.md
# The cast/party worker portraits (generated/characters/*.png) ARE used by the
# floating cast and worker cards (story.js castPortraitSrc), so they must ship -
# otherwise every worker face 404s in a fresh clone / the deployed app. Only the
# 7 top-level character PNGs ship; the heavy alt-art (_v1_prewakanda/) and motion
# (characters/video/) subdirs stay local-only via the *.png/*.mp4 rules below.
!generated/characters/
!generated/characters/*.png
!generated/lore/
!generated/lore/*.png
# Lore background stills (MAI-generated, ours under MIT) ship too, so the
# onboarding first-step screen has its art on a fresh clone.
!generated/lore/*.jpg
# Baked narration takes (tools/generate_narration.py) ship committed - the
# directed cinematic voice is the baseline every fork hears, no keys needed.
!generated/lore/narration/
!generated/lore/narration/*.mp3
# Motion clips are a local-only progressive enhancement - mostly too heavy to
# commit, and the committed MAI stills are the baseline every fork gets.
# EXCEPTION: the single assembled intro film (film.voiced.mp4, ~50MB) ships
# committed so a fresh `git clone` plays the cinematic with no setup; the
# tracked film.png still is the graceful fallback. Superseded per-scene clips
# (old_v2/) and raw render frames (frames/) stay local-only.
generated/lore/video/*
*.mp4
*.webm
*.mov
!generated/lore/video/film.voiced.mp4
